#Neon Nebula:

# Click on the link to test the code:
https://subhamsuvam.github.io/NeonSpace/

Hello I am Subham and I have created an arcade-style space collection game with RPG elements, power-ups, and AI opponents. Built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

#Features:

1. Dual Game Modes
  - Solo Mode: Survive and collect as many points as possible
  - VS Comouter Mode: Race against computer opponents to reach 10 points first

2. Difficulty Levels
  - Easy, Medium, and Hard challenges for both game modes

3. Persistent Progression System
  - User accounts with local storage
  - Earn galactic credits by playing
  - Purchase and upgrade power-ups

4. Power-Up System
  - Shield: Temporary invincibility (upgradable duration)
  - Speed Boost: Increased movement speed (upgradable duration)
  - Each power-up can be upgraded to level 15

5. Leaderboard
  - Track high scores across all players
  - Compare wallet balances

6. Responsive Controls
  - Keyboard support (Arrow Keys)
  - Touch-friendly on-screen buttons for mobile devices

#How to Play

1. Create an Account - Register with username, age, and password
2. Earn Points - Collect green orbs, avoid red asteroids
3. Upgrade - Use points to buy and upgrade power-ups
4. Compete - Try to beat your high score or challenge the AI

#Controls

| Action | Keyboard | Touch/Mobile |
|--------|----------|---------------|
| Move Up | ↑ Arrow | On-screen ↑ button |
| Move Down | ↓ Arrow | On-screen ↓ button |
| Move Left | ← Arrow | On-screen ← button |
| Move Right | → Arrow | On-screen → button |
| Shield | Click power-up icon | Tap shield button |
| Speed Boost | Click power-up icon | Tap boost button |

#Scoring System

1. Green Orbs: +1 point each
2. Red Asteroids: Game over (unless shield is active)
3. VS Computer Mode: First to 10 points wins

#Point Rewards
- Each collected orb = 1 galactic credit
- Points can be spent in the Power-up Lab

#Technical Details

#Built With
- HTML5 Canvas for game rendering
- CSS3 with animations and glassmorphism effects
- Vanilla JavaScript (no external dependencies)
- Local Storage for data persistence
- Web Audio API for sound effects

#Data Structure
javascript
User Object {
  username: string,
  password: string,
  age: number,
  highScore: number,
  totalPoints: number,
  shieldStock: number,
  boostStock: number,
  sLvl: number (0-15),
  bLvl: number (0-15)
}

